	<text>
		<body>
				<p rend="align(center)"><placeName>San Francisco</placeName> <date>Jany 25th 1864&#8212;5624</date>.</p>
				<p><addressee>Revd Isaac Leeser</addressee></p>
			<p rend="indent(1)"><placeName>Philadelphia</placeName></p>
			<p rend="indent(2)">My dear Sir</p>
			<p rend="indent(4)">I hope ere this reaches you&#44; you will have<lb/> received the mss<add>&#63;</add> of the &#8220;Reflections on <add>Hebrew</add>&#8221; &#38;c and that<lb/> it will suit your Journal.  I now send you the balance of the said article&#8212;<lb/> I hope by this time you will have quite recovered from you indisposition.  I sent<lb/> you by last mail a pamphlet of the History of the Polish Jews which I translated<lb/> from the French.  I should hope you have received it.  I must observe to you<lb/> that should my articles not suit you&#44; please return the mss<add>&#63;</add> as I have no copy<lb/> I do not mind the Postage I will return the amt of stamps required&#8212;but I hope<lb/> you will find my work acceptable and if so I will from time to time employ<lb/> my leisure hours to write for your Occident for I consider that to be the best<lb/> Jewish magazine in the whole <placeName>United States</placeName> without any flattery&#44; I read it at<lb/> all times with pleasure.  I take opportunity to mention that I shall so on remit<lb/> you some money&#44; my <sic>Income</sic> is very limited and every thing is very high in<lb/> <placeName>California</placeName> which keeps me poor&#44; but never mind&#44; <hi rend="underline">better late than never</hi><lb/> I will shortly send you some statistics of <placeName>San Francisco</placeName> Jewish matters&#8212;at present<lb/> all is still.  Some short time ago <persName>Mr de Solla</persName> formerly of <placeName>Jamaica</placeName> wrote<lb/> some articles for the &#8220;Hebrew&#8221; on Angels &#38; Devils&#44; I suppose you have read them<lb/> I have commenced a critique on the subject&#44; I will finish it and send it to<lb/> you if you like to publish it in the occident. <sic>let</sic> me hear from you in return<lb/> Praying for your improved health</p>
			<p rend="indent(10)">Believe me yours truly</p>
			<p rend="indent(11)"><persName role="author">H. A. Henry</persName></p>
				<p>PS.</p>
				<p>You must not scold me for writing on</p>
				<p>both sides of the paper&#44; I know it is not</p>
				<p>so good for the composition&#44; but I do it to save postage.  Still if you do not like it&#44; I</p>
				<p>will do otherwise in future.  <persName role="author">H. A. Hy</persName></p>
		</body>
	</text>
